reviewsJson.markdown:
**Percentage Used:** 6%

&nbsp;

**Equipment Used:**  Troll RDA with a single Kanthal .3 ohm Staircase coil at 27W. 24g kernel with 32g wrap, cotton wick.

&nbsp;

**PG/VG:** 30/70

&nbsp;

**Steep Time:** 3 Days and 4 Weeks

&nbsp;

**Aroma:** Mixed fresh berries. Sweet. 

&nbsp;

**Flavor Description:** Strawberry and blackberry hit first. Raspberry marionberry, and boysenberry? Not detecting any blueberry, but almost a red huckleberry faintly? Tastes like a blend of fresh and artificial fruit. At 4 weeks this has transformed into a very naturally sweet mix of berries. Refreshing and juicy seeded berries, and I no longer get any artificial flavors. Strawberry, raspberry, and blackberry seem the most obvious. A hint of blueberry in the back. I'm sure there are more, but I can't pick them out individually. These do have a  slightly more vibrant and brighter flavor than other mixed berries I have tried. Maybe that is the wild part?

&nbsp;

**Off Flavors:** None

&nbsp;

**Throat Hit:** 2/10

&nbsp;

**Pairings:** Almost any fruit, apples, grapes, cranberries. Cakes scones, biscuits. cobblers, cereal, creams, custards, nuts, tobaccos, fruit drinks, candy, gummy candy. Doughnut , pastries.

&nbsp;

**Notes:** This is a good strength for a single flavor in an RDA. If using a tank I would recommend 8-10%. As an accent flavor maybe 1.5-3% I am already working on a yummy Wild Berry shortcake with a big mound of whipped cream.
